 When considered on the binary tree topology, its derivative looks a lot
 less intimidating: in fact, it is perfectly well-defined on the leaves;
 the only ambiguity is on the interior nodes of the tree.
 Furthermore, the interior nodes of the tree are a countable set, whereas
 the leaves are uncountable.
 
